SINGLE CASK UNBLENDED

THOSE RARE COGNACS which have been distilled, aged and estate-bottled in France by small producers are completely in a class apart. It requires patience, belief in the future, and will power on the part of a small grower to resist the immediate cash tempta- tion offered him by the big Cognac distillers to set aside his best brandy of a great year; leave it untouched for decades, and then finally put it on the market. Because of the simple life and relative wealth of Marcel Ragnaud, this is precisely what he did in order to create this unblended, entirely remarkable Grand Fine Champagne Cognac.

It is certainly not the most expensive Cognac on our shelves, but, candidly, we think the Cognac fancier would be hard put to find a better example of Cognac any- where in France, regardless of age or price. In terms of quality, ‘Single Cask’ is simply extraordinary.
